column5: I'm working on  an new website to try and stress the fact that Nipissing has more than just walleye in it.  I'm looking for some decent pictures of some of the best bass (both) perch, pike, muskie etc. you have caught on Nipissing!  Lets see em!!  (LOL)  Ill take sunsets and scenery as well!!
Here's a few Nippissing muskies bud
Holy cow lew! Those are some monsters!
Just get lucky sometimes sterling LOL
Thanks Lew!!  . youre my muskie picture, that big smile and all!!
Always happy to oblige with a smile TJ
All my fish pics from Nipissing are walleye, so here's a sunset from a week or two ago.
Lew ive never seen someone so happy to catch a musky in my life!
Have a look at what's on my website: http://www.southriverresort.com/Photos.  Let me know what you'd like and I'll send you a hi-res copy if I have it.
A hallmark
A hallmark  Oh the memories.....or was it the mammaries?
A hallmark the women in that place looked rougher than the men....not that I would know this first hand.....
My Summer and Winter Nip pictures are locked away in a vault TJ just in case I ever need to use 'em.......
A hallmark  I should upload a more recent picture... the place is in shambles now.
Here are my favourites
Here's a few Nippissing muskies bud                      Now I know why you gave up fishing...You've caught them all !!!
A hallmark  Oh Boy...  LOL..  Cant say I ever remember being in there ... wink...   lol

If that place was The Mo Z On Inn, I was never there either a few times. What was the name of the place downtown, dancin' girls during the day and a singles bar at night that I was never in either if the weather blew us off the lake during the day.  I have some Bear Creek pictures but they are either faded or are in black and white.
Fantastic shots!!!
Now I know why you gave up fishing...You've caught them all !!! He sure didn't look like he was having fun fishing . . . . so why not . . .
